{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"plain-withe-pedal","description":"## What\nThe release workflow `.github/workflows/release.yml` publishes `nava-rebar` to PyPI on a `vX.Y.Z` tag but never creates a **GitHub Release**. The v0.2.0/v0.3.0 GitHub Releases were created by hand and that manual step lapsed, so github.com/navapbc/rebar shows **v0.3.0 as Latest** while tags and all three channels (PyPI, Homebrew, MCP Registry) advanced to **v0.6.0**. `docs/releasing.md` does not mention the GitHub Release channel at all.\n\n## Why\nGitHub's Releases page is the human-facing \"what's the latest version\" surface. It being 3 versions stale is misleading to users and contributors.\n\n## Fix (two parts)\n- **Backfill (ops):** create GitHub Releases for the missing tags `v0.4.0`, `v0.5.0`, `v0.5.1`, `v0.5.2`, `v0.6.0` with auto-generated notes so `Latest` points at v0.6.0 now.\n- **Process (code, via Gerrit):** add a job/step to `.github/workflows/release.yml` that creates a GitHub Release on every `v*` tag push (auto-generated notes, marked latest), and document the channel in `docs/releasing.md`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] GitHub Releases exist for v0.4.0, v0.5.0, v0.5.1, v0.5.2, v0.6.0 and `gh release list` shows v0.6.0 as `Latest`.\n- [ ] `.github/workflows/release.yml` creates a GitHub Release automatically on a `v*` tag push (with `contents: write` on that job and auto-generated notes).\n- [ ] `docs/releasing.md` documents the GitHub Release channel/step.\n- [ ] Change lands on main through Gerrit (both LLM-Review and Verified votes green).","id":"f112-6222-e236-4b09","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Automate GitHub Release creation in release.yml + backfill v0.4.0–v0.6.0"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783300460201998001,"uuid":"a6c0fd5c-17d2-4510-9d97-770983401531"}